<p>Below is a translation of <a href="https://youtu.be/7-5lxR83Kdg?t=4007">my dadâ€™s prayer</a>, which he gave after his March 13 sermon on John 2:1-12, on Jesus turning water into wine.</p>

<p>Most Korean prayers Iâ€™ve heardâ€“and I have heard  thousandsâ€“are elevated and drawn out. So translating Korean prayers is tricky. One would never <em>write</em> a prayer in this way. Spoken, it can make sense, according to my dad.</p>

<p>-</p>

<p><strong>Translation</strong></p>

<p><em>Holy Father God</em><br />
<em>thank You</em><br />
<em>for because You love us You made us people of Your Kingdom</em><br />
<em>and thank You</em> <br />
<em>for You lead us to live</em> <br />
<em>in Your abundant love and</em> <br />
<em>the abundant grace of Your Kingdom</em><br />
<em>You who can do all things</em><br />
<em>answers everything</em><br />
<em>and promises that all things will be accomplished in Jesus Christ.</em></p>

<p><em>But moment by moment we feel lack and want.</em></p>

<p><em>In those times</em> <br />
<em>we lift our faces</em> <br />
<em>and raise our heads</em><br />
<em>and lift our souls</em>        <br />
<em>so that through seeing Jesus Christ with faith â€“</em><br />
<em>He</em><br />
<em>Who turns water into wine</em><br />
<em>Who transforms our living souls</em><br />
<em>Who makes our weakness strong</em><br />
<em>Who fills our lack with abundant things â€“</em><br />
<em>grant us to be Your precious children who can live blessed lives</em><br />
<em>in which Your power and the wonderful signs of Your kingdom are realized in our everyday lives.</em></p>

<p><em>In the name of Jesus we pray</em><br />
<em>Amen.</em></p>

<p>-</p>

